metadata.synopsis: The portrait of filmmaker Jacques Demy follows his formative years in 1940s Nantes, France.

reviews: A portrait that is at once a love letter to the movies, a critical perspective on one of its celebrated artist's, and a personal tribute.
It is a film about a boy who knew what he loved to do in life and was fortunate to make a living doing it.
It is not a sad film, however. It is a film about a boy lucky enough to discover how he wanted to spend his life, and to spend it that way.
